    <h1>PAINT&#xAD;ING WITH LIGHT</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201016/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-10-16"><time>2020-10-16</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Na­tional Gallery Sin­ga­pore’s fes­ti­val of in­ter­na­tional films about art re­turns for its third edi­tion.</p>
    <p>This time, how­ever, it is all on­line and free.</p>
    <p>From Viet­nam comes the short drama Sweet, Salty (PG13, 18 min­utes, left), about Ha, a preg­nant woman whose hus­band ap­pears to have aban­doned their home for his mis­tress’ place.</p>
    <p>Friends and fam­ily goad her into con­fronting the mis­tress, dur­ing which Ha makes an un­ex­pected dis­cov­ery.</p>
    <p>This work, from Viet­namese film-maker Duong Dieu Linh, was se­lected for the Sin­ga­pore In­ter­na­tional Film Fes­ti­val last year, where it won the Youth Jury Prize. WHERE: Na­tional Gallery Sin­ga­pore’s Paint­ing With Light web­site</p>
    <p>WHEN: Till Oct 25</p>
    <p>AD­MIS­SION: Free</p>
    <p>INFO: na­tion­al­gallery.sg/ paint­ing­with­light</p>

